    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is because d2 is computed with ddof=1 by default and in d0 when np.std(data) is called directly ddof=0.\n\nWe probably need to add documentation regarding this\n\nIn [9]: d0\nOut[9]: \n2010-06-30         NaN\n2010-09-30   -0.774981\n2010-12-31   -0.090074\n2011-03-31   -1.228296\n2011-06-30   -2.095889\n2011-09-30    1.068140\n2011-12-31   -0.479264\nFreq: Q-DEC\n\nIn [13]: d2 = ts.resample('Q', how=lambda x: np.std(x, ddof=0))\n\nIn [14]: d1 / d2\nOut[14]: \n2010-06-30         NaN\n2010-09-30   -0.774981\n2010-12-31   -0.090074\n2011-03-31   -1.228296\n2011-06-30   -2.095889\n2011-09-30    1.068140\n2011-12-31   -0.479264\nFreq: Q-DEC\n"
