    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Closing this issue as this is indeed the result of pandas intercepting `np.std` and using a faster function that uses an `n - 1` divisor (what people usually expect, `ddof=0` has always struck me as an odd default given the behavior of most other statistical computing environments). To force `ddof=0` you would have to do the trick that @changhiskhan suggested, forcing ddof=0\n"
